Identity & Entity Nexus (IDN)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the canonical data definitions (DATADEF) for the Identity & Entity Nexus (IDN).
It provides:
semantic meaning of each core field
invariants and constraints
cross-engine usage expectations
authoritative reference for audits and integrations
This document is the field-level contract complementing NS-IDN-007 — DATAMODEL.
2. DATADEF Principles
Semantic Immutability — field meaning never changes
Canonical IDs Only — cross-engine references use canonical IDs
Temporal Explicitness — time-bound fields are explicit
Explainability — every mutation has rationale
Audit Completeness — no derived-only truth
3. Actor Data Definitions
3.1 actor
Field
Definition
Notes
actor_id
Canonical actor identifier
Stable forever
actor_type
Classification of actor
human / agent / service / org
status
Current lifecycle state
active / suspended / retired
created_at
Creation timestamp (UTC)
Immutable
Invariants:
actor_id never changes
status transitions are governed
4. Entity Data Definitions
4.1 entity
Field
Definition
Notes
entity_id
Canonical entity identifier
Stable forever
entity_type
Entity classification
legal / property / product / account / concept
lifecycle_state
Entity lifecycle
proposed / active / archived
created_at
Creation timestamp (UTC)
Immutable
Invariants:
entity_id never changes
lifecycle_state changes are explicit
5. Identifier Data Definitions
5.1 identifier
Field
Definition
Notes
identifier_id
Identifier record ID
Internal
identifier_type
Type of identifier
email / tax_id / platform_id
identifier_value
Normalized identifier value
Case/format normalized
issuing_system
Source system
Required
confidence_score
Confidence in correctness
Optional
created_at
When identifier observed
UTC
Invariants:
identifier_value is immutable
identifiers are never reassigned silently
6. Identifier Link Definitions
6.1 identity_identifier_link
Field
Definition
Notes
subject_type
actor or entity
Required
subject_id
Canonical ID
actor_id or entity_id
identifier_id
Linked identifier
FK
linked_at
Link timestamp
UTC
unlinked_at
Unlink timestamp
Nullable
Semantics:
unlinked_at indicates deprecation, not deletion
7. Relationship Data Definitions
7.1 relationship
Field
Definition
Notes
relationship_id
Relationship identifier
Internal
source_type
actor/entity
Required
source_id
Canonical source ID
Stable
target_type
actor/entity
Required
target_id
Canonical target ID
Stable
relationship_type
Edge meaning
owns / manages / controls
effective_from
Start of validity
UTC
effective_to
End of validity
Nullable
Invariants:
open relationships have effective_to = null
updates close old edges, create new ones
