10. Cross-Engine Contract Expectations
Engine
IDN Contract
GGP
Uses identity + decision artifacts for governance
SIG
Attributes signals using canonical IDs
PIE
Groups insights by entity
SIM
Binds scenarios to entities
DAT
Executes actions on behalf of entities
FLO
Accounts financial state per entity
PECA
Creates new legal/property entities
CWP
Manages agentic actors
Downstream engines must not cache identity snapshots.
11. Validation & Constraints
All timestamps are UTC
Canonical IDs are UUIDs
Identifier uniqueness enforced per (type, value, issuing_system)
Relationship type must be valid for source/target types
12. Backward Compatibility Rules
Fields may be added but never removed
Field meaning never changes
Deprecated fields remain readable
13. Document Position in IDN Corpus
This DATADEF completes the IDN documentation set.
It complements:
NS-IDN-007 — DATAMODEL
NS-IDN-006 — VERSION
